WEBVTT

00:01.109 --> 00:02.568
Maybe you don't know
how babies are made.

00:02.569 --> 00:05.310
Because when people are trying,
they know they're trying!

00:05.311 --> 00:07.247
And just because no one
ever wants to try with you

00:07.248 --> 00:08.748
doesn't give you the right

00:08.750 --> 00:10.516
to tell me how to run
my associates!

00:10.518 --> 00:12.485
I think Rachel should
handle the associates.

00:12.487 --> 00:15.021
I am up here;
Rachel's down here.

00:15.023 --> 00:16.422
And you don't give dominion
over the associates

00:16.424 --> 00:18.190
to someone down here.

00:18.192 --> 00:19.592
Which one of my clients
are you after?

00:19.594 --> 00:21.360
Because we both know
you can't have Pfizer.

00:21.362 --> 00:23.496
- Yes, I can.
- Then make me name partner.

00:23.498 --> 00:25.331
Harvey's making his friend
name partner.

00:25.333 --> 00:26.766
He's accused me
of being jealous,

00:26.768 --> 00:28.467
and I don't know what to do.

00:28.469 --> 00:30.469
- Are you jealous?
- Of course I'm goddamn jealous!

00:30.471 --> 00:33.572
If you keep letting your
emotions dictate your behavior,

00:33.574 --> 00:36.308
you won't need to worry
about being replaced.

00:36.310 --> 00:38.477
You'll drive Harvey away
all by yourself.

00:38.479 --> 00:40.813
Stop apologizing
and start intimidating.

00:40.815 --> 00:42.214
That's a hell of a slogan,
Harvey,

00:42.216 --> 00:43.783
but what does it actually mean?

00:43.785 --> 00:45.785
It means you go out,
you find a reporter,

00:45.787 --> 00:47.486
and you control the narrative.

00:47.488 --> 00:49.522
If I lose this case,
the only article that's

00:49.524 --> 00:51.357
gonna get written is that
I never should've been able

00:51.359 --> 00:53.059
to practice law
in the first place.

00:53.061 --> 00:55.161
If you can't figure out
a way to win,

00:55.163 --> 00:56.796
<i>maybe I shouldn't have brought</i>
<i>you back in the first place.</i>

00:56.798 --> 00:58.397
A reporter from
the "Times" is coming here.

00:58.399 --> 01:00.232
We are doing an interview:

01:00.234 --> 01:02.635
"The Redemption
of a Fraudulent Lawyer."

01:02.637 --> 01:05.137
I don't want my behavior

01:05.138 --> 01:06.605
to drive a wedge between us,

01:06.607 --> 01:09.141
which means I accept Alex
as name partner.

01:09.143 --> 01:10.543
For what it's worth,
Alex is still coming,

01:10.545 --> 01:12.078
but not as name partner.

01:12.080 --> 01:13.479
- Really?
- You're right.

01:13.481 --> 01:15.001
We can't water down
the firm like that.

01:18.653 --> 01:21.854
I have to say... [laughs]

01:21.856 --> 01:23.856
I've been wanting this
for so long.

01:23.858 --> 01:27.560
Never in my wildest dreams
did I think it would come true.

01:28.830 --> 01:31.330
We're the only name partners
now, Louis.

01:31.332 --> 01:33.566
And I meant it
when I said it.

01:33.568 --> 01:35.434
I want us to share
things like this.

01:35.436 --> 01:38.537
I can't tell you how
happy that makes me.

01:38.539 --> 01:40.406
You're not gonna
cry, are you?

01:40.408 --> 01:41.440
Are you kidding?
The last time I cried in here,

01:41.442 --> 01:43.109
I messed up the pH.

01:43.111 --> 01:44.577
I had a yeast infection
for weeks.

01:44.579 --> 01:46.445
You're not gonna do the other
thing you told me

01:46.447 --> 01:48.547
you did in the mud, are you?

01:48.549 --> 01:50.649
Harvey, I told you,
that was a one-time thing.

01:50.651 --> 01:52.518
And believe me,
you're no Missy Dietler.

01:52.520 --> 01:54.286
Who's Missy Dietler?

01:54.288 --> 01:56.655
- What is he doing here?
- What do you mean?

01:56.657 --> 01:58.691
Harvey and I go mudding together
all the time.

01:58.693 --> 02:00.392
So why don't you lug yourself
out of there

02:00.394 --> 02:03.129
so I can get my tub back?
This is my tub.

02:03.131 --> 02:04.597
And you always told me it was
weird for male friends

02:04.599 --> 02:06.465
to mud together.

02:06.467 --> 02:09.201
But Harvey and I are
more than just friends.

02:09.203 --> 02:10.369
We're best friends.

02:14.208 --> 02:15.608
And then what did you do?

02:15.610 --> 02:17.143
What do you think I did?
I called you.

02:17.145 --> 02:19.345
Louis, it was just a dream.

02:19.347 --> 02:21.347
Just a dream?
It was a goddamn mud-mare.

02:21.349 --> 02:22.681
Don't you get it?

02:22.683 --> 02:24.350
Harvey let his buddy
into my firm.

02:24.352 --> 02:26.185
Now he's in my mud.

02:26.187 --> 02:27.553
I mean, what's next?
I walk into my bathroom

02:27.555 --> 02:28.888
and I find him shitting
on my toothbrush?

02:28.890 --> 02:30.456
Louis, we talked about this.

02:30.458 --> 02:32.424
If you let this
overwhelm you,

02:32.426 --> 02:35.361
you're going to bring about
the thing you're most afraid of.

02:36.564 --> 02:38.164
Did you hear me?

02:38.166 --> 02:39.932
He was in my mud.

02:39.934 --> 02:42.434
How the hell am I not supposed
to let that overwhelm me?

02:42.436 --> 02:44.270
Well...

02:44.272 --> 02:46.238
has it occurred to you

02:46.240 --> 02:48.908
that instead of worrying
this Alex person

02:48.910 --> 02:51.510
is going to come between you
and Harvey,

02:51.512 --> 02:54.313
you could use this
as an opportunity

02:54.315 --> 02:56.649
to make a new friend?

02:56.651 --> 02:58.684
That's the dumbest thing
I've ever heard.

02:58.686 --> 03:00.319
Be that as it may,

03:00.321 --> 03:02.254
as I see it,

03:02.256 --> 03:05.257
you have a chance to have
one more friend

03:05.259 --> 03:07.259
or one less friend.

03:07.261 --> 03:09.261
I suggest you go with one more.

03:09.263 --> 03:12.965
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

03:12.967 --> 03:14.300
- Donna.
- Rachel.

03:14.302 --> 03:16.302
Can I get you two
anything?

03:16.304 --> 03:18.737
Coffee, tea, a copy of your
article in the "Sunday Times"?

03:18.739 --> 03:21.307
Don't need it. Read it
yesterday. Have one at home.

03:21.309 --> 03:23.309
And by one, he means ten.

03:23.311 --> 03:24.643
Are you sure you don't want to
take just one more look at it?

03:24.645 --> 03:26.512
I'm good.
Thanks, Donna.

03:26.514 --> 03:28.314
Okeydokey.

03:28.316 --> 03:29.415
You have a nice day.

03:30.785 --> 03:33.485
Something's going on with her,
I can tell.

03:33.487 --> 03:35.487
What do you mean?

03:35.489 --> 03:38.257
You telling me you didn't
notice that grin on her face?

03:38.259 --> 03:40.259
Rachel, you've known Donna
longer than I have,

03:40.261 --> 03:41.660
but I didn't see a grin.

03:41.662 --> 03:43.422
I'm telling you,
I think you're imagining it.

03:45.433 --> 03:47.800
Right. Totally imagined it.

03:47.802 --> 03:50.336
Harvey.
Rachel.

03:50.338 --> 03:52.404
You know,
black can be slimming.

03:52.406 --> 03:54.273
Something to think about
next time.

03:54.275 --> 03:55.674
I take it this is your
way of apologizing

03:55.676 --> 03:57.676
for saying you never
should've hired me back.

03:57.678 --> 03:59.778
And it gave me a chance to say
the slimming thing.

04:01.449 --> 04:03.549
Sorry, Mike.

04:03.551 --> 04:05.317
You had a point, Harvey.

04:10.324 --> 04:11.991
This is the Radiant
Technologies merger.

04:11.993 --> 04:13.659
Yep. Back to one for me.

04:13.661 --> 04:15.594
Great, except you don't
need me for this.

04:15.596 --> 04:17.529
Deal's done.
They sign tomorrow.

04:17.531 --> 04:19.832
Which is why Klein Robinson
thought that I wouldn't mind

04:19.834 --> 04:22.034
if they put a few last-minute
changes in the contract.

04:22.036 --> 04:23.736
And a few last-minute changes
means they're trying to pull

04:23.738 --> 04:25.638
some last-minute bullshit.

04:25.640 --> 04:27.039
Now that sounds like
the impressive young lawyer

04:27.041 --> 04:28.774
I read about in the article.

04:28.776 --> 04:30.376
Why don't you figure out
what they're trying to do?

04:30.378 --> 04:32.678
And get it done by lunch.

04:35.850 --> 04:37.549
Who says I need slimming?

04:42.323 --> 04:45.858
<i>♪ See the money,</i>
<i>wanna stay for your meal ♪</i>

04:45.860 --> 04:49.495
<i>♪ Get another piece of pie</i>
<i>for your wife ♪</i>

04:49.497 --> 04:52.631
<i>♪ Everybody wanna know</i>
<i>how it feel ♪</i>

04:52.633 --> 04:56.435
<i>♪ Everybody wanna see</i>
<i>what it's like ♪</i>

04:56.437 --> 04:59.371
<i>♪ I'll even eat a bean pie,</i>
<i>I don't mind ♪</i>

04:59.373 --> 05:03.309
<i>♪ Me and Missy is so busy,</i>
<i>busy making money ♪</i>

05:03.311 --> 05:04.810
<i>♪ All right ♪</i>

05:04.812 --> 05:06.049
<i>♪ All step back,</i>
<i>I'm 'bout to dance ♪</i>

05:06.050 --> 05:10.050
<b><font color="#00FF00">♪ Suits 7x03 ♪</font></b>
