05:15.223 --> 05:17.357
[exhales] Don't be hostile.

05:17.359 --> 05:18.658
Don't be hostile.

05:18.660 --> 05:20.026
Louis, what are you doing?

05:20.028 --> 05:21.060
- What?
- Leave him alone.

05:21.062 --> 05:22.662
It's his first day.

05:22.664 --> 05:23.663
No, Donna, it's not like that.
I come in peace.

05:23.665 --> 05:25.098
You swear?

05:25.100 --> 05:26.766
Yes, I brought him
a living thing.

05:26.768 --> 05:29.168
- Is it poisonous?
- No, Donna, it is not.

05:29.170 --> 05:31.838
Okay. Well, I got
my eyes on you.

05:31.840 --> 05:34.040
And that plant.

05:34.042 --> 05:36.109
[exhales heavily]
Don't be hostile.

05:37.312 --> 05:39.145
Alex Williams, Louis Litt.

05:39.147 --> 05:40.146
I brought you a honeysuckle.

05:40.148 --> 05:42.215
Excuse me?

05:42.217 --> 05:44.651
It's a gesture, since we
might've gotten off

05:44.653 --> 05:46.319
on the wrong foot.

05:46.321 --> 05:47.720
You mean because you tried
to poach my biggest client

05:47.722 --> 05:49.322
and keep me from joining
the firm?

05:49.324 --> 05:51.424
Yes, perhaps that's the foot
we got off on.

05:51.426 --> 05:55.094
But I was hoping we could
get onto other foot.

05:55.096 --> 05:57.163
Here.

05:57.165 --> 05:59.866
I appreciate the gesture,
Louis.

05:59.868 --> 06:03.770
By the way, your work on the
Andersen case was extraordinary.

06:03.772 --> 06:05.738
You followed my Andersen work?

06:05.740 --> 06:08.408
Yes. In fact, it reminded me
of my Pricehouse strategy.

06:08.410 --> 06:11.210
Truth be told, I based it
on your Pricehouse strategy.

06:11.212 --> 06:13.446
Get the f--well then, you took
it to a whole other level.

06:13.448 --> 06:15.682
[chuckles]
Thank you, Louis.

06:16.885 --> 06:19.152
I'm sorry about the poaching.

06:19.154 --> 06:20.687
Don't worry about it.

06:20.689 --> 06:22.855
[sighs contentedly]

06:22.857 --> 06:25.291
Hey, would you
like to grab lunch?

06:25.293 --> 06:28.361
Eating at your desk is no way to
celebrate your first day.

06:28.363 --> 06:30.329
You're right, it's not.

06:30.331 --> 06:31.898
I'll meet you at the lobby
at 1:00.

06:31.900 --> 06:33.800
Sounds good.
And thanks for the plant.

06:33.802 --> 06:35.702
You're welcome.

06:35.704 --> 06:37.270
I don't know if you care
about this, but cats love it.

06:37.272 --> 06:39.405
Oh, I know.
We've got two tabbies at home

06:39.407 --> 06:40.940
that are gonna go crazy
over that bad boy.

06:40.942 --> 06:42.709
- Tabbies?
- Yup.

06:42.711 --> 06:44.444
Holy shit, I'm gonna make
a reservation

06:44.446 --> 06:47.480
at the best restaurant
in the city, you... BFF, you.

06:48.783 --> 06:50.183
Son of a bitch.

06:52.487 --> 06:53.886
Mr. Reyes?

06:53.888 --> 06:55.755
- Yes.
- Mike Ross.

06:55.757 --> 06:57.223
They said you
wanted to see me?

06:57.225 --> 06:58.291
Yes, thank you for
taking the time.

06:58.293 --> 07:00.827
Of course.

07:00.829 --> 07:03.930
I read your interview
yesterday.

07:03.932 --> 07:05.832
And my son was
in prison too.

07:05.834 --> 07:08.868
But unlike you,

07:08.870 --> 07:10.903
he didn't make it out.

07:12.407 --> 07:14.307
This says your son died
of a heart attack.

07:14.309 --> 07:16.809
-Yes, a heart attack out
of nowhere.

07:16.811 --> 07:18.277
You think they're
hiding something.

07:18.279 --> 07:19.512
Well, they won't
take my calls

07:19.514 --> 07:21.414
or answer my letters.

07:21.416 --> 07:23.149
What would you think?

07:23.151 --> 07:24.817
I'd think that there
might be something wrong.

07:24.819 --> 07:27.453
But that doesn't
mean that there is.

07:27.455 --> 07:29.989
Mr. Ross, my son
was 28 years old.

07:29.991 --> 07:32.425
And he was up for
parole next month.

07:32.427 --> 07:34.427
There's something
they're not telling me.

07:34.429 --> 07:36.362
All right,
I'll look into it.

07:36.364 --> 07:40.399
Um, but I'm not gonna be able
to get to this for a few days.

07:40.401 --> 07:42.902
A few days.
Why can't you start now?

07:42.904 --> 07:45.371
Because I have a deal
with my firm that allows me

07:45.373 --> 07:48.307
to do cases like this,
but not only cases like this.

07:48.309 --> 07:50.376
And right now, I'm in the middle
of something else.

07:50.378 --> 07:53.312
Mr. Ross, the last
lawyer I talked to

07:53.314 --> 07:55.448
said there was some kind
of a statute

07:55.450 --> 07:58.851
that says I only have another
two weeks to file a lawsuit.

07:58.853 --> 08:01.420
And I'm telling you, two weeks
should be more than enough time,

08:01.422 --> 08:05.491
but I--I can't drop everything
just to take your case.

08:05.493 --> 08:07.326
I understand.

08:07.328 --> 08:09.028
But...

08:09.030 --> 08:12.398
Chris was caught with
an ounce of marijuana.

08:12.400 --> 08:14.333
He never should have been there
in the first place.

08:14.335 --> 08:16.435
And if time runs out on this

08:16.437 --> 08:21.274
and I couldn't get him
justice...

08:21.276 --> 08:23.543
Okay.

08:23.545 --> 08:25.278
I'll see what I can do.

08:28.550 --> 08:30.983
Stephanie, we need to talk
about this assignment.

08:30.985 --> 08:32.552
Is there a problem with it?

08:32.554 --> 08:34.986
Yes, the problem is
you didn't do it.

08:34.989 --> 08:36.923
Jason did.

08:36.924 --> 08:40.592
Because Jason is better at
cataloging procedure than I am.

08:40.595 --> 08:42.461
Right, but if you don't do
the things you're not good at,

08:42.462 --> 08:44.063
you'll never get better.

08:44.065 --> 08:45.398
The thing is, I don't really
want to get better

08:45.400 --> 08:47.333
at cataloging procedure.

08:47.335 --> 08:49.335
I know that, just like
I didn't want to be a paralegal

08:49.337 --> 08:51.971
specializing in research for
as long as I was.

08:51.973 --> 08:54.607
But it turns out we
had a case last year

08:54.609 --> 08:57.944
that we only won because I was
outstanding at research.

08:59.881 --> 09:01.280
Okay, I see your point.

09:01.282 --> 09:03.516
I won't do it again.
Good.

09:03.518 --> 09:06.252
Because I have another case
that requires some procedure

09:06.254 --> 09:09.055
to be catalogued, and I put it
aside especially for you.

09:11.359 --> 09:12.959
But Stephanie, I want your word

09:12.961 --> 09:15.528
that you won't pawn
it off on Jason.

09:15.530 --> 09:17.330
You have my word.

09:20.969 --> 09:23.436
[phone buzzing]

09:25.874 --> 09:28.074
Well, look who it is.

09:28.076 --> 09:30.576
Don't tell me, you feel bad
about canceling the other night

09:30.578 --> 09:32.078
and now you're dying
to make it up to me.

09:32.080 --> 09:34.013
It's as though you read
my mind.

09:34.015 --> 09:36.015
<i>One of my many skills.</i>

09:36.017 --> 09:38.017
How does dinner tonight sound?

09:38.019 --> 09:40.353
How does having it
at my place sound?

09:40.355 --> 09:41.554
You're a crafty one,
aren't you?

09:41.556 --> 09:43.289
What? I've got some steaks

09:43.291 --> 09:44.957
I've been wanting to throw
on the grill.

09:44.959 --> 09:46.592
No, you want to have dinner
at your place

09:46.594 --> 09:47.894
'cause it's the closest
restaurant in the city

09:47.896 --> 09:49.428
to your bedroom.

09:49.430 --> 09:50.563
Did you read that
in "Zagat's"?

09:50.565 --> 09:52.331
No, I read your mind.

09:52.333 --> 09:53.900
Then what time am I thinking?

09:53.902 --> 09:55.568
How about 8:00?

09:55.570 --> 09:57.570
Better make it 8:30.
I got to go buy some steaks.

10:00.909 --> 10:02.541
Good, you're here.

10:02.543 --> 10:03.576
Tell me you figured out
what bullshit they're trying

10:03.578 --> 10:05.444
to sneak into this deal.

10:05.446 --> 10:06.913
They're not trying to sneak
anything into it.

10:06.915 --> 10:08.614
They're trying to
get out of it.

10:08.616 --> 10:10.683
That doesn't make sense.
They came to us for this merger.

10:10.685 --> 10:12.318
They must've gotten
a better offer,

10:12.320 --> 10:13.319
because they buried
an escape clause

10:13.321 --> 10:15.121
in the addendum.

10:15.123 --> 10:17.690
- You know what we have to do.
- Yes, I do.

10:17.692 --> 10:20.126
But you're gonna have
to do it without me.

10:20.128 --> 10:21.527
Something's come up,
it's on a deadline,

10:21.529 --> 10:23.162
and I need to take care of it.

10:23.164 --> 10:25.131
- What kind of thing?
- A pro Bono thing.

10:25.133 --> 10:27.667
Since when does one for me
mean two for you?

10:27.669 --> 10:30.603
Harvey, a man died in prison
and it doesn't smell right.

10:30.605 --> 10:32.505
Also, the only reason I found
out about it is

10:32.507 --> 10:34.106
I took your advice
and did that interview.

10:34.108 --> 10:35.942
So it's my fault
that you're dropping my case?

10:35.944 --> 10:37.643
Yeah, I like to look at it
that way.

10:37.645 --> 10:41.147
Seriously, go get 'em.

10:41.149 --> 10:42.448
Thanks, Harvey.

10:45.520 --> 10:47.353
The last guy brought me
a plant.

10:47.355 --> 10:48.988
Let me guess,
the last guy was Louis.

10:48.990 --> 10:50.656
- You got it.
- Well, I guarantee

10:50.658 --> 10:52.591
my welcome gift is a lot
more fun than his.

10:52.593 --> 10:54.493
Since when is a merger
signing fun?

10:54.495 --> 10:56.629
Since the guys on the other
side are trying to rip us off

10:56.631 --> 10:58.397
and think we don't know.

10:58.399 --> 10:59.966
Why didn't you tell me that in
the first place?

10:59.968 --> 11:01.600
Come on. I'll fill you in
on the way over.

11:01.602 --> 11:03.602
Wait, the meeting's now?

11:03.604 --> 11:04.971
Yeah, is that a problem?

11:04.973 --> 11:06.739
I told Louis we'd get lunch.

11:06.741 --> 11:08.641
Business trumps lunch.
Louis'll understand.

11:08.643 --> 11:10.242
Just call him
and let him know.

11:14.215 --> 11:15.982
[phone ringing]

11:17.085 --> 11:18.985
Alex, hi, I was just on my way
to meet you.

11:18.987 --> 11:20.686
<i>About that, Louis.</i>
<i>I have to reschedule.</i>

11:20.688 --> 11:22.989
A work thing came up.
I hope you understand.

11:22.991 --> 11:24.390
<i>Yeah, of course.</i>

11:24.392 --> 11:27.193
Business comes first.
Thanks.

11:27.195 --> 11:29.275
We'll do it another time.
In fact, I'm free all week.

11:30.732 --> 11:33.466
Louis? You okay?

11:33.468 --> 11:35.001
Uh, yeah, I'm okay.

11:35.003 --> 11:38.004
I, uh--
it's allergy season.

11:38.006 --> 11:40.539
I--I think it's probably best
that we don't have lunch today.

11:40.541 --> 11:43.609
I, uh--my--my chest
feels like a vice.

11:45.546 --> 11:46.679
All good?

11:46.681 --> 11:48.247
I think so.

11:48.249 --> 11:50.249
What kind of plant
did he get you, anyway?

11:50.251 --> 11:52.752
- Honeysuckle.
- Huh.

11:52.754 --> 11:54.153
I never knew that
was an indoor plant.

11:54.155 --> 11:55.688
Can be.

11:55.690 --> 11:57.490
Matter of fact, our cats
are gonna love it.

11:57.492 --> 12:00.559
- You have cats?
- Why you gotta be like that?

12:00.561 --> 12:02.661
- Why you gotta have cats?
- I like my cats.

12:02.663 --> 12:04.497
No, you don't.

12:04.499 --> 12:07.099
[laughing]

12:12.540 --> 12:15.541
Ms. Snyder? Mike Ross.

12:15.543 --> 12:17.510
Is that name supposed to mean
something to me?

12:17.512 --> 12:20.579
No, but I'm representing
the family of Chris Reyes.

12:22.216 --> 12:23.449
Hoping that name does.

12:23.451 --> 12:24.817
Of course.

12:24.819 --> 12:26.118
Any time an inmate dies,

12:26.120 --> 12:28.054
we take it very seriously.

12:28.056 --> 12:29.722
But not seriously enough to
give an accounting of his death

12:29.724 --> 12:32.158
despite repeated requests
by his family.

12:32.160 --> 12:34.193
I received no such requests.

12:34.195 --> 12:35.661
It's a shame you didn't
call first.

12:35.663 --> 12:37.196
I could've prepared
something.

12:37.198 --> 12:38.697
I didn't want you
to be prepared,

12:38.699 --> 12:40.566
'cause I want to know what
actually happened.

12:40.568 --> 12:42.601
Mr. Ross,
when you do what I do,

12:42.603 --> 12:44.570
you get used to people assuming
the worst about your company,

12:44.572 --> 12:46.105
so I would appreciate
a little respect.

12:46.107 --> 12:47.606
Ms. Snyder, when
you do what I do,

12:47.608 --> 12:49.141
you get used to companies
proving you right,

12:49.143 --> 12:52.645
so I would appreciate
a little action.

12:59.754 --> 13:02.555
Apparently Mr. Reyes
was in a fight.

13:02.557 --> 13:04.323
He was sent to solitary,
where he complained

13:04.325 --> 13:06.092
of difficulty breathing.

13:06.094 --> 13:08.127
A doctor was called
and delivered treatment.

13:08.129 --> 13:10.129
Unfortunately, he died
a few hours later.

13:10.131 --> 13:11.630
Well, if he was in a fight,

13:11.632 --> 13:13.532
there has to be
an incident report.

13:13.534 --> 13:15.534
That may be, but you have
no right to access it.

13:15.536 --> 13:17.169
We're a private corporation.
That's privileged.

13:17.171 --> 13:18.571
Okay, then how about
you give me

13:18.573 --> 13:20.172
the names of the guards
who saw it?

13:20.174 --> 13:21.874
You know I can't give you
that either.

13:21.876 --> 13:23.342
And you know that if I bring
a suit against you,

13:23.344 --> 13:25.144
I'm gonna get all
of this anyway.

13:25.146 --> 13:28.114
So why don't you save yourself
the publicity

13:28.116 --> 13:29.715
and just give it to me now?

13:36.760 --> 13:38.927
I don't care what that
thing says.

13:38.929 --> 13:41.029
It's not the whole story.

13:41.031 --> 13:43.265
Mr. Reyes, I know this isn't
what you wanted to hear,

13:43.267 --> 13:44.966
but I'm not seeing a case.

13:44.968 --> 13:47.702
It says there that my son

13:47.704 --> 13:49.638
died alone in solitary
confinement.

13:49.640 --> 13:50.872
Why didn't they take him
to an infirmary?

13:50.874 --> 13:52.574
Because he was seen
by a doctor.

13:52.576 --> 13:53.909
There was an explanation
for his symptoms.

13:53.911 --> 13:55.810
I know you think
I'm just a man

13:55.812 --> 13:57.879
who can't accept
his child's death.

13:57.881 --> 13:59.814
But that's not true.

13:59.816 --> 14:02.083
Mr. Reyes, a fight in prison
can elevate your heart rate.

14:02.085 --> 14:03.752
Nobody knows that
better than I do.

14:03.754 --> 14:06.755
What they're saying happened
is plausible.

14:06.757 --> 14:08.590
Then you didn't know my son.

14:08.592 --> 14:11.259
I told you, he was up
for parole next month.

14:11.261 --> 14:13.328
He wouldn't have gotten
into a fight.

14:13.330 --> 14:15.330
What exactly are you saying?

14:15.332 --> 14:16.665
One of those inmates

14:16.667 --> 14:18.967
must have come for him.

14:18.969 --> 14:21.336
And that prison didn't give
enough of a shit about Chris

14:21.338 --> 14:23.772
to protect him.

14:23.774 --> 14:25.574
Mr. Reyes, I know that
you came to me

14:25.576 --> 14:27.008
because that article said
I wanted to help people

14:27.010 --> 14:29.611
and I do, but...

14:29.613 --> 14:32.113
I know.
My son's already dead.

14:32.115 --> 14:35.016
But if they could've
stopped this and they didn't,

14:35.018 --> 14:37.118
it's going to happen again.

14:37.120 --> 14:40.121
<i>[somber music]</i>

14:40.123 --> 14:45.794
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:45.796 --> 14:48.830
Chase, I'd like you to meet
our newest senior partner,

14:48.832 --> 14:50.665
Alex Williams.

14:50.667 --> 14:52.634
Two senior partners just
to sign a contract.

14:52.636 --> 14:54.336
Seems excessive.

14:54.338 --> 14:56.838
It would be, but we're
not here to sign anything.

14:56.840 --> 14:57.973
What are you talking about?

14:57.975 --> 14:59.774
He must think I'm pretty dumb.

14:59.776 --> 15:01.610
People always underestimate
a pretty face.

15:01.612 --> 15:02.911
Maybe he just thinks
you're dumb.

15:02.913 --> 15:04.613
'Cause of the droopy eyes.

15:04.615 --> 15:06.615
Valid theory.
Not unprecedented.

15:06.617 --> 15:08.049
Nobody thinks you're dumb.

15:08.051 --> 15:09.651
Then why the hell did you
sneak this clause

15:09.653 --> 15:11.353
to the back of my
goddamn contract?

15:11.355 --> 15:12.921
We didn't sneak anything.

15:12.923 --> 15:14.789
We were just looking
at our options.

15:14.791 --> 15:16.858
Bullshit. You're trying
to use us as a stalking horse

15:16.860 --> 15:18.927
so you can merge with Gorban.

15:18.929 --> 15:20.895
So what if I was?

15:20.897 --> 15:22.731
What are you going to do
to stop it?

15:22.733 --> 15:24.733
I'll tell you what I did.
I called Alex.

15:24.735 --> 15:27.335
And what I did was call my
law school roommate at the DOJ

15:27.337 --> 15:29.337
about the anti-trust issues
raised by you

15:29.339 --> 15:30.639
merging with Gorban.

15:32.943 --> 15:34.409
What do you want?

15:34.411 --> 15:36.111
We want you to live up
to the terms

15:36.113 --> 15:38.680
of the original agreement.
With one exception.

15:38.682 --> 15:40.749
You're gonna
take a step down.

15:40.751 --> 15:42.851
- I'm not stepping down.
- Yes, you are.

15:42.853 --> 15:45.654
This new company doesn't need
two outside counsels.

15:45.656 --> 15:47.756
Particularly one who tries
to pull shady shit

15:47.758 --> 15:49.858
without his client
knowing about it.

15:49.860 --> 15:51.826
Looks like you're gonna
take one for the team, Chase.

15:51.828 --> 15:56.097
The question is, would you like
to bow out or get kicked out?

15:56.099 --> 15:59.100
<i>[tense music]</i>

15:59.102 --> 16:02.037
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:02.039 --> 16:03.838
<i>How the hell</i>
<i>can I calm down?</i>

16:03.840 --> 16:05.373
<i>I was watching my mud-mare</i>
<i>come true.</i>

16:05.375 --> 16:07.108
You don't know
what you saw, Louis.

16:07.110 --> 16:09.010
<i>I'm sorry, I forgot</i>
<i>I was blind.</i>

16:09.012 --> 16:11.379
I must've dialed your number
using my Braille-a-phone.

16:11.381 --> 16:13.014
You know that's not
what I meant.

16:13.016 --> 16:14.816
No, you're right,
it's the only explanation

16:14.818 --> 16:16.751
as to why I wouldn't
know what I just saw,

16:16.753 --> 16:19.988
which was Harvey and Alex,
arm in arm, laughing at me!

16:19.990 --> 16:22.157
Louis, listen to me.

16:22.159 --> 16:24.025
We knew this was
going to happen.

16:24.027 --> 16:25.794
That I was gonna be betrayed
by my best friend?

16:25.796 --> 16:27.796
No, that you were going to try
to be good--

16:27.798 --> 16:29.864
<i>- Did it.</i>
- Try not to be you.

16:29.866 --> 16:31.232
<i>- Accomplished.</i>
- Then perceive

16:31.234 --> 16:33.134
a potentially
nonexistent slight

16:33.136 --> 16:36.104
and go straight
to stage seven.

16:36.106 --> 16:37.872
What the hell are you
talking about?

16:37.874 --> 16:40.208
<i>Panic, sorrow, self-loathing,</i>

16:40.210 --> 16:45.980
hatred, justification,
self-loathing again, and rage.

16:45.982 --> 16:48.483
I call it
the seven stages of Louis.

16:48.485 --> 16:50.118
You are so full of shit,

16:50.120 --> 16:52.887
and you're a total fraud,
and I'm actually gonna--

16:52.889 --> 16:54.456
ah, uh, I see your point.

16:54.458 --> 16:56.991
Stage 7b.

16:56.993 --> 16:59.260
No one likes a gloater, Stan.

16:59.262 --> 17:01.229
Be that as it may.

17:01.231 --> 17:02.997
You need a strategy, Louis.

17:02.999 --> 17:05.165
For now and the next time
this happens.

17:05.167 --> 17:07.435
[sighs]
The breathing exercises.

17:07.436 --> 17:09.804
<i>It's the only thing</i>
<i>that's ever worked for you.</i>

17:09.806 --> 17:11.239
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:11.241 --> 17:14.175
What would I do
without you, Doc?

17:14.176 --> 17:17.979
No need to go down
that road, my friend.

17:17.981 --> 17:22.117
Now, picture yourself near
the ocean,

17:22.118 --> 17:24.051
<i>laying in the sand.</i>

17:24.054 --> 17:25.987
<i>Isn't it lovely?</i>

17:28.925 --> 17:30.058
I got to say,
that was pretty fun.

17:30.060 --> 17:31.926
I agree.

17:31.928 --> 17:34.062
I always wanted to pretend I had
a friend at the DOJ.

17:34.064 --> 17:35.230
Not a bad first day.

17:35.232 --> 17:37.298
Speaking of my first day,

17:37.300 --> 17:39.000
what's up with that
Louis Litt guy?

17:39.002 --> 17:41.136
- What do you mean?
- I don't know.

17:41.138 --> 17:42.504
First he tries to stop me
from coming over,

17:42.506 --> 17:44.038
then he brings me a plant,

17:44.040 --> 17:45.940
then when I called
to cancel lunch,

17:45.942 --> 17:48.209
I could've sworn he was
about to cry or something.

17:48.211 --> 17:49.811
What?

17:51.515 --> 17:53.982
Louis is...

17:53.984 --> 17:55.550
he's complicated.

17:55.552 --> 17:58.052
What do you mean,
complicated?

17:58.054 --> 18:00.321
Well, you know he didn't
want you here, right?

18:00.323 --> 18:02.791
The thing is,
it wasn't professional.

18:02.793 --> 18:05.126
What else could it be?

18:05.128 --> 18:06.795
He was worried that
I was gonna be

18:06.797 --> 18:08.263
better friends
with you than him.

18:08.265 --> 18:10.832
[scoffs] What the hell
is wrong with this guy?

18:10.834 --> 18:12.066
Does he have a crush on you?

18:12.068 --> 18:13.902
No.

18:13.904 --> 18:16.070
Yeah, he totally
has a crush on me.

18:16.072 --> 18:17.806
But not like that.

18:17.808 --> 18:20.208
Maybe this'll work.
You ever seen "MASH"?

18:20.210 --> 18:22.277
Of course, but what does that
have to do with this?

18:22.279 --> 18:24.579
Louis is Frank Burns.

18:24.581 --> 18:26.214
Oh.

18:26.216 --> 18:28.183
Why didn't you say so
in the first place?

18:28.185 --> 18:29.317
Now I totally get it.

18:29.319 --> 18:31.019
- You sure?
- Yeah.

18:31.021 --> 18:33.288
He loves you, hates you,
and wants to be you,

18:33.290 --> 18:34.856
all at the same time.

18:34.858 --> 18:35.990
Huh, you do get it.

18:35.992 --> 18:38.860
Yeah, I do.
The question is,

18:38.862 --> 18:40.361
are you sure he's gonna
be okay with me,

18:40.363 --> 18:41.996
or do I have to watch out?

18:41.998 --> 18:43.998
Well, let me ask you this.

18:44.000 --> 18:46.100
Did you tell him your cats
are gonna love his honeysuckle?

18:46.102 --> 18:47.368
Yes.

18:47.370 --> 18:48.603
Then I think
you'll be fine.

18:52.576 --> 18:55.243
Excuse me.
You guys know Chris Reyes?

18:55.245 --> 18:57.111
Doesn't ring a bell.

18:57.113 --> 18:59.180
That's strange, 'cause
according to the incident report

18:59.182 --> 19:01.149
the three of you were on duty
the night he died.

19:01.151 --> 19:03.017
Even if I were, I wouldn't
have anything to say about it,

19:03.019 --> 19:04.886
so you can get the fu--
out of here.

19:04.888 --> 19:05.920
Hey, come on. I just have
a few questions, that's all.

19:05.922 --> 19:07.222
This is a prison.

19:07.224 --> 19:08.857
All questions go through
the main office.

19:08.859 --> 19:10.258
Where do you think
I got your names?

19:10.260 --> 19:12.026
I don't give a shit
where you got 'em.

19:12.028 --> 19:14.028
You're gonna forget
you ever heard 'em.

19:14.030 --> 19:15.864
And if I see your face again,
there's gonna be a problem.

19:15.866 --> 19:17.966
Okay, look, I'm not trying
to start any trouble here.

19:17.968 --> 19:20.301
But a man is dead, and I need
to find out what happened.

19:20.303 --> 19:22.203
For a guy who's not looking
to cause any trouble,

19:22.205 --> 19:23.605
you sure don't listen too good.

19:23.607 --> 19:25.039
Come on, Drew.
Let's go.

19:25.041 --> 19:26.307
That's what he wants.

19:26.309 --> 19:28.042
I'm telling you,
he's not worth it.

19:28.044 --> 19:31.045
<i>[tense music]</i>

19:31.047 --> 19:36.184
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:40.991 --> 19:42.624
You're one of those assholes
who just love

19:42.626 --> 19:44.192
getting the shit beat
out of him, aren't you?

19:44.194 --> 19:45.927
No, I've had the shit
beat out of me,

19:45.929 --> 19:47.328
and I can tell you,
I didn't love it at all.

19:47.330 --> 19:48.429
Then you better get the hell
out of here

19:48.431 --> 19:50.198
before it happens again.

19:50.200 --> 19:52.333
I will, just as soon
as you answer my questions.

19:52.335 --> 19:54.068
And why would I do that?

19:54.070 --> 19:56.137
Because your name is
at the top of the list,

19:56.139 --> 19:58.406
and I'm guessing
you know what that means.

19:58.408 --> 20:00.642
Yeah, I'm the scapegoat.

20:00.644 --> 20:02.610
But it also means anything they
get, they know it came from me.

20:02.612 --> 20:04.145
Except you just told me
to go to hell

20:04.147 --> 20:05.680
in front of all your buddies,

20:05.682 --> 20:08.683
and they saw you meant it.

20:08.685 --> 20:11.219
That's why you came to me
at the prison.

20:11.221 --> 20:13.688
Now you got cover.

20:13.690 --> 20:16.291
And I suggest you use it.

20:16.293 --> 20:18.226
Because I am gonna find out
what happened here,

20:18.228 --> 20:20.929
and when I do, they are gonna
shield themselves from liability

20:20.931 --> 20:23.064
and I am gonna end up
coming after you instead.

20:23.066 --> 20:25.633
Or you can tell me
what I need to know,

20:25.635 --> 20:27.302
and I'll leave you out of it.

20:29.940 --> 20:31.039
I'm the one who pulled him
out of the fight

20:31.041 --> 20:33.041
and threw him in the hole.

20:33.043 --> 20:35.243
He started complaining saying he
was having problems breathing.

20:35.245 --> 20:37.679
I told my supervisor, and my
supervisor said he was gonna

20:37.681 --> 20:39.414
call the doctor.

20:39.416 --> 20:42.083
That's all I know.
Bullshit that's all you know.

20:42.085 --> 20:43.418
Look, did Chris get killed
because he was onto something?

20:43.420 --> 20:45.420
- No.
- Well, that kid,

20:45.422 --> 20:47.255
he didn't just up and get
in a fight without good reason.

20:47.257 --> 20:48.423
You don't know what
you're talking about.

20:48.425 --> 20:49.991
Look, are the guards corrupt?

20:49.993 --> 20:51.693
What the hell
did you just say?

20:51.695 --> 20:53.995
- Was somebody out to get him?
- No, he just died!

20:53.997 --> 20:55.396
Look, there's no conspiracy.

20:55.398 --> 20:56.998
Nobody's evil.

20:57.000 --> 20:58.499
Just cheap.

20:58.501 --> 21:00.368
What does that mean?

21:00.370 --> 21:02.136
It means the only reason they
were able to wale on him

21:02.138 --> 21:03.671
for as long as they did is
'cause they didn't have

21:03.673 --> 21:05.406
enough of us on duty that night,

21:05.408 --> 21:07.008
'cause the prison doesn't give
a shit about anything

21:07.010 --> 21:08.309
except its bottom line.

21:14.753 --> 21:16.920
So what did you do?

21:16.922 --> 21:18.522
So I told him he could
have the money,

21:18.524 --> 21:19.857
but if--if he tried
taking those albums,

21:19.859 --> 21:21.525
we're gonna have trouble.

21:21.527 --> 21:24.161
[laughs]

21:25.798 --> 21:27.030
This was lovely.

21:28.968 --> 21:30.801
But I have an early
morning tomorrow.

21:30.803 --> 21:32.536
I think I should get home.

21:32.538 --> 21:35.005
Paula, what's going on?

21:35.007 --> 21:36.106
It's nothing.

21:36.108 --> 21:38.709
Really.
Nothing?

21:38.711 --> 21:40.110
We had a great night.

21:40.112 --> 21:41.879
All of a sudden
you have to go?

21:41.881 --> 21:43.747
You wouldn't understand.

21:43.749 --> 21:45.182
Try me.

21:47.887 --> 21:50.754
I had lunch with the woman who
was my mentor today.

21:50.756 --> 21:51.989
And we were having
a wonderful time

21:51.991 --> 21:53.056
catching up with each other,

21:53.058 --> 21:54.858
and then... out of the blue,

21:54.860 --> 21:57.094
she asked me if I
was seeing anyone.

21:57.096 --> 21:59.096
I said no.

21:59.098 --> 22:00.998
Well, we haven't exactly
been seeing each other

22:01.000 --> 22:02.866
for very long.
It's understandable if you--

22:02.868 --> 22:04.535
No, it wasn't that, Harvey.

22:05.905 --> 22:08.872
It's that I felt a little...
What?

22:08.874 --> 22:10.941
Ashamed.

22:10.943 --> 22:12.876
Ashamed.

22:12.878 --> 22:14.311
This isn't a small thing,
what we're doing, Harvey.

22:14.313 --> 22:16.947
At least it's not to me.
It's not to me either.

22:16.949 --> 22:21.018
Well, I'm not sure I realized
exactly how not small it is

22:21.020 --> 22:23.020
until today.

22:23.022 --> 22:24.021
I don't understand.
We've been over this.

22:24.023 --> 22:25.756
It's in writing.

22:25.758 --> 22:27.324
There's no violation with
us seeing each other.

22:27.326 --> 22:28.926
This isn't something that I am

22:28.928 --> 22:30.027
trying to get away with,
Harvey.

22:30.029 --> 22:32.095
It's how I'm feeling inside.

22:33.832 --> 22:36.166
- So what are you saying?
- I'm not saying anything.

22:36.168 --> 22:40.604
I'm just saying I think I should
sleep at my place tonight.

22:40.606 --> 22:43.607
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

22:43.609 --> 22:47.978
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:47.980 --> 22:50.247
Donna, I need to talk to you
about something.

22:50.249 --> 22:51.882
About what?

22:51.884 --> 22:53.050
About the fact that
I'm pissed off.

22:53.052 --> 22:54.785
What's going on?

22:54.787 --> 22:56.153
I gave Stephanie Patel
an assignment

22:56.155 --> 22:57.621
and she handed it off.

22:57.623 --> 22:59.056
Did you talk to her about it?

22:59.058 --> 23:00.624
Yes, I did, and she
gave me her word

23:00.626 --> 23:02.626
that she would never
do it again, but she did.

23:02.628 --> 23:04.194
I don't understand.
This has Stephanie's name on it.

23:04.196 --> 23:05.862
I don't care whose
name is on it.

23:05.864 --> 23:06.930
There's no way that
that wasn't written

23:06.932 --> 23:08.332
by a first-year associate.

23:08.334 --> 23:09.900
Rachel, please tell me you're
not thinking

23:09.902 --> 23:11.068
about going to Louis with this.

23:11.070 --> 23:12.336
Are you kidding me?

23:12.338 --> 23:14.104
We took Louis off the associates

23:14.106 --> 23:16.139
because of his
incident with Stephanie.

23:16.141 --> 23:19.209
If I tell him that she's being
insubordinate, he'll kill her.

23:19.211 --> 23:21.244
Well, I can't believe
I'm saying this,

23:21.246 --> 23:25.048
but maybe you should take a page
out of Louis' book.

23:25.050 --> 23:26.650
What do you mean?

23:26.652 --> 23:28.285
When Louis first took over
the associates,

23:28.287 --> 23:31.188
he used to plant a fake
associate and fire him

23:31.190 --> 23:32.990
in front of the entire class
on day one.

23:32.992 --> 23:34.958
And I used to think
he was crazy,

23:34.960 --> 23:37.194
but Stephanie never would have
pulled something like this

23:37.196 --> 23:38.362
with Louis.
Okay, first of all,

23:38.364 --> 23:40.263
that's just not
how I operate.

23:40.265 --> 23:42.232
And second of all,
they've all been here.

23:42.234 --> 23:44.001
They'd all be able to tell
that it was fake.

23:44.003 --> 23:46.937
Then maybe you need
to real fire her.

23:46.939 --> 23:49.272
Because this is a second offense
and if you keep letting it go,

23:49.274 --> 23:50.374
where does it end?

23:50.376 --> 23:52.009
I'm not gonna do that.

23:52.011 --> 23:53.377
Do you mind if I ask you
why not?

23:53.379 --> 23:55.245
Because I don't want my
first official act

23:55.247 --> 23:57.147
to be firing someone.
I understand that, Rachel.

23:57.149 --> 23:58.982
But you better think
of something.

23:58.984 --> 24:00.984
Because the one thing
that Louis understood

24:00.986 --> 24:02.986
was that you've got to come out
of the gate in command,

24:02.988 --> 24:04.988
or they're gonna
walk all over you.

24:04.990 --> 24:11.094
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:11.096 --> 24:12.262
Yes?

24:12.264 --> 24:14.264
Mr. Reyes, it's Mike Ross.

24:14.266 --> 24:15.666
I went to the prison, and I
talked to one of the guards.

24:15.668 --> 24:17.668
What did he say?

24:17.670 --> 24:19.903
He said all the prison cares
about is their bottom line.

24:19.905 --> 24:22.439
So I'm filing a lawsuit tonight.

24:22.441 --> 24:24.941
Thank you so much, Mr. Ross.

24:26.412 --> 24:29.112
I thought that article was maybe
too good to be true.

24:29.114 --> 24:31.682
I appreciate that, Oscar,
but don't thank me

24:31.684 --> 24:33.717
until I get you
the answers you're looking for.

24:33.719 --> 24:40.957
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:43.195 --> 24:45.429
You finished
the paperwork already?

24:45.431 --> 24:47.297
I might have to give you
a raise.

24:47.299 --> 24:48.999
Save your money, Harvey.

24:49.001 --> 24:50.000
I'm here about something else.

24:50.002 --> 24:51.435
What's going on?

24:51.437 --> 24:53.437
I just heard Mike Ross
is handling a pro bono.

24:53.439 --> 24:56.339
Yeah, we have a deal. Why?
You need him for something?

24:56.341 --> 24:59.342
Yeah, I need him
to drop that case.

24:59.344 --> 25:01.211
Why?

25:01.213 --> 25:02.713
Because there's a conflict
with Masterson Construction.

25:02.715 --> 25:04.414
Mike's pro bono is against
some prison.

25:04.416 --> 25:06.016
And guess who builds
those prisons.

25:06.018 --> 25:07.350
Wait a second.

25:07.352 --> 25:09.152
Are you telling me to go
back on my word

25:09.154 --> 25:10.721
because your client's
bullying you?

25:10.723 --> 25:12.222
Harvey, I thought
we were in this together.

25:12.224 --> 25:13.924
- So did I.
- Then get on board.

25:13.926 --> 25:15.058
Because they're not
just any client.

25:15.060 --> 25:16.460
They're one of my biggest.

25:16.462 --> 25:18.395
And if they leave
because you chose some prisoner

25:18.397 --> 25:20.063
over one of the biggest
developers in the country,

25:20.065 --> 25:21.765
people are gonna get the message

25:21.767 --> 25:23.734
that we don't want to be
in the real estate business.

25:23.736 --> 25:25.135
Did they say they were gonna
give people that message?

25:25.137 --> 25:26.737
- Harvey--
- Did they or not?

25:26.739 --> 25:28.205
- They did.
- Drop 'em.

25:28.207 --> 25:29.406
- God damn it--
- I said drop 'em.

25:29.408 --> 25:30.741
- No.
- Excuse me?

25:30.743 --> 25:32.309
I may not be name partner yet,

25:32.311 --> 25:34.111
but you don't get to tell me
who my clients are.

25:34.113 --> 25:35.212
Yes, I do.

25:35.214 --> 25:37.414
Harvey, listen to yourself.

25:37.416 --> 25:39.382
It's one pro bono.
He just took it.

25:39.384 --> 25:41.084
He can drop it.

25:43.288 --> 25:44.988
I gave him my word.

25:44.990 --> 25:46.389
And you once gave
your word to me

25:46.391 --> 25:48.391
and went back on it
and I let it go.

25:48.393 --> 25:50.494
Because I understood
it was business.

25:50.496 --> 25:53.029
If this kid doesn't get that,
what the hell is he doing here?

26:00.239 --> 26:03.273
Stephanie, I asked you to come
to my office.

26:03.275 --> 26:04.541
That was over an hour ago.

26:04.543 --> 26:06.243
I was working on
the Sanderson brief.

26:06.245 --> 26:07.778
I was about to come down.

26:07.780 --> 26:09.446
Well, I need to talk
to you now,

26:09.448 --> 26:11.214
because you told me that
you wouldn't hand this off,

26:11.216 --> 26:13.083
and you did.

26:13.085 --> 26:14.518
No, I told you that I wouldn't
hand it off to Jason,

26:14.520 --> 26:16.386
and I didn't.

26:16.388 --> 26:17.420
I'm sorry, are you trying
to get out of this

26:17.422 --> 26:19.156
on a technicality?

26:19.158 --> 26:21.491
I'm your supervisor,
not opposing counsel.

26:21.493 --> 26:24.194
Rachel, I tried to be nice
about this,

26:24.196 --> 26:26.363
but I'm a fourth-year associate,

26:26.365 --> 26:27.998
and I'm not wasting my time

26:28.000 --> 26:29.533
on something a first-year
could handle.

26:29.535 --> 26:32.169
Now, if you don't mind, I would
like to get back to work.

26:33.338 --> 26:35.071
Actually, I do mind.

26:35.073 --> 26:37.574
Excuse me, Stephanie,
I'm speaking to you.

26:37.576 --> 26:40.110
It doesn't matter
what year you are.

26:40.112 --> 26:41.444
I'm head of the associates.

26:41.446 --> 26:43.380
If I give you an assignment,
you do it.

26:43.382 --> 26:45.515
And when you give me one
that's worth my time, I will.

26:45.517 --> 26:46.550
What's going on here?

26:46.552 --> 26:48.285
Donna, I'm handling it.

26:48.287 --> 26:50.020
What's going on is
that I am a grown woman,

26:50.022 --> 26:51.354
and I don't need to be
told what to do by someone

26:51.356 --> 26:53.557
with less experience
as a lawyer than me.

26:53.559 --> 26:55.425
Then you're really gonna
hate being told what to do

26:55.427 --> 26:57.460
by someone with no experience
as a lawyer.

26:57.462 --> 26:59.162
- Donna--
- Excuse me?

26:59.164 --> 27:00.597
I said, you're here,
and I'm here.

27:00.599 --> 27:02.399
So unless you want
to deal with me,

27:02.401 --> 27:04.868
you'll listen when Rachel
tells you something.

27:04.870 --> 27:08.138
I was recruited to come here.

27:08.140 --> 27:10.340
And I was told that
I would be valued

27:10.342 --> 27:12.142
for my mind, my billings,

27:12.144 --> 27:13.577
and my relationship
with my clients.

27:13.579 --> 27:15.312
And since I got here,

27:15.314 --> 27:17.314
I have had to take shit
from Louis.

27:17.316 --> 27:19.549
And now you're asking me
to waste my time and my ability

27:19.551 --> 27:21.184
on something like this.

27:21.186 --> 27:23.119
- Okay--
- You're right, Stephanie.

27:23.121 --> 27:24.454
You shouldn't have been
treated like that by Louis.

27:24.456 --> 27:26.156
And Rachel and I
took care of it.

27:26.158 --> 27:28.258
Now as for your
time and ability,

27:28.260 --> 27:30.460
if you don't do whatever
assignment Rachel gives you,

27:30.462 --> 27:32.429
I don't give a shit
how good you are.

27:32.431 --> 27:34.197
We are gonna show you the door.

27:34.199 --> 27:37.200
<i>[somber music]</i>

27:37.202 --> 27:44.307
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:52.675 --> 27:54.586
Hey. Did you come by
to tell me

27:54.588 --> 27:56.021
that the work I did
saved your ass?

27:56.023 --> 27:59.357
It did, but that's
not why I'm here.

27:59.359 --> 28:00.992
Harvey, what's going on?

28:00.994 --> 28:03.461
You have to drop
your pro bono.

28:03.463 --> 28:04.929
There's a conflict with one
of our clients.

28:04.931 --> 28:06.031
What? Who?
I checked for conflicts

28:06.033 --> 28:07.932
before I took the case.

28:07.934 --> 28:09.000
- It's a new client.
- Well, if it's a new client,

28:09.002 --> 28:10.468
then let's drop them.

28:10.470 --> 28:11.936
We can't.
They're a huge developer.

28:11.938 --> 28:13.338
A developer?
I'm suing a prison.

28:13.340 --> 28:14.706
I know that,
but they're saying--

28:14.708 --> 28:16.474
I don't care what
they're saying.

28:16.476 --> 28:17.575
That's not a conflict.
That's a shakedown.

28:17.577 --> 28:18.977
- Mike--
- No.

28:18.979 --> 28:20.078
You're gonna give me
the green light,

28:20.080 --> 28:22.314
and then I find something,

28:22.316 --> 28:23.348
and then you're gonna make me
dump them for no good reason?

28:23.350 --> 28:24.916
It's not no good reason.

28:24.918 --> 28:27.385
It's Alex's developer,
and I just brought him in.

28:27.387 --> 28:28.953
I let him lose one
of his biggest clients

28:28.955 --> 28:30.989
his first week here,
it's a disaster.

28:30.991 --> 28:32.691
And I let a man die
without getting him justice.

28:32.693 --> 28:34.559
What the hell is that?
Listen to me--

28:34.561 --> 28:36.428
Listen to yourself.
We had a deal.

28:36.430 --> 28:38.563
Now this clown is asking me
to drop a client

28:38.565 --> 28:40.398
that I made a promise to.

28:40.400 --> 28:42.367
Except he's not asking you
to drop him, Mike.

28:42.369 --> 28:46.071
I am. And if you don't,
that deal we made--it's over.

28:53.647 --> 28:55.046
How could you do that?

28:55.048 --> 28:57.015
Do what? I was helping you.

28:57.017 --> 28:59.651
No, Donna, you were
undermining me.

28:59.653 --> 29:01.386
Undermining you?

29:01.388 --> 29:03.054
You needed backup.
That's what I'm here for.

29:03.056 --> 29:05.023
No, I needed to handle
the situation,

29:05.025 --> 29:07.525
which is what I was doing
until you decided to interfere

29:07.527 --> 29:09.627
in something that you don't
know anything about.

29:09.629 --> 29:12.097
No offense, Rachel, but I did
know something about it,

29:12.099 --> 29:14.132
and from what I could tell,
you weren't handling it at all.

29:14.134 --> 29:16.067
And you think what you did
was any better?

29:16.069 --> 29:18.136
I think I told you that you
need to set the tone early on.

29:18.138 --> 29:20.071
Okay, and the tone
that you just set

29:20.073 --> 29:23.608
is that if you're not there,
she can walk all over me.

29:23.610 --> 29:24.709
Well, I don't know
what room you were in,

29:24.711 --> 29:26.544
but she was doing that anyway.

29:26.546 --> 29:28.012
And what does it say about me
if the other associates

29:28.014 --> 29:29.781
see me letting her do that?

29:29.783 --> 29:31.750
What it says is that you
trust my leadership style

29:31.752 --> 29:33.518
instead of thinking that you
need to fight my fights for me.

29:33.520 --> 29:35.086
Stephanie needed
what I gave her.

29:35.088 --> 29:37.389
And if you think that was
me fighting your fights,

29:37.391 --> 29:38.490
you don't know what
you're talking about.

29:38.492 --> 29:39.691
Because if it were up to me,

29:39.693 --> 29:40.759
I would've fired her
on the spot.

29:40.761 --> 29:42.160
Well then, why didn't you?

29:42.162 --> 29:43.628
Because they're not
my associates.

29:43.630 --> 29:44.996
You're right.
They're mine.

29:44.998 --> 29:46.131
And I fought for you
to get them.

29:46.133 --> 29:47.966
And you just belittled me

29:47.968 --> 29:50.402
and embarrassed me
in front of all of them.

29:50.404 --> 29:51.703
And that is not something that I

29:51.705 --> 29:53.805
thought my friend
would do to me.

29:53.807 --> 29:55.573
Well, you know what, I never
thought I would say this,

29:55.575 --> 29:57.575
but maybe you weren't
ready for your new position.

29:57.577 --> 29:59.043
Well, you know what, Donna?

29:59.045 --> 30:00.612
Maybe neither were you.

30:05.152 --> 30:07.719
Dr. Lipschitz, I, uh--
I know you're in a session.

30:07.721 --> 30:09.554
I just wanted to say
that you were right.

30:09.556 --> 30:11.689
Uh, I was overreacting.

30:11.691 --> 30:13.558
I do not have a problem
with Alex.

30:13.560 --> 30:15.660
And, uh, if I ever
get triggered again,

30:15.662 --> 30:17.662
I have the deep breathing.

30:17.664 --> 30:19.197
Anyway, thanks again.

30:19.199 --> 30:21.065
Auf Wiedersehen.

30:21.067 --> 30:22.734
- [sighs discontentedly]
- Mike.

30:22.736 --> 30:24.602
It's good to see you.

30:24.604 --> 30:26.471
This'll just take a few minutes,
and then it's all yours.

30:26.473 --> 30:28.473
No, it doesn't matter
how long it takes, Louis.

30:28.475 --> 30:30.208
We can just charge the time
back to some client, right?

30:30.210 --> 30:32.177
'Cause nobody around here
gives a shit about anything

30:32.179 --> 30:33.478
other than making money anyway.

30:33.480 --> 30:35.447
Mike, what is going on?

30:35.449 --> 30:37.115
What's going on is that
the only reason I came back here

30:37.117 --> 30:38.516
is that Harvey and I
made a deal,

30:38.518 --> 30:39.851
and it hasn't even
been a week,

30:39.853 --> 30:41.719
and he's already going
back on it.

30:41.721 --> 30:42.754
Whoa, whoa, whoa, that's not
gonna happen on my watch.

30:42.756 --> 30:44.456
Okay? So just slow down.

30:44.458 --> 30:46.138
Tell me what the hell
you're talking about.

30:50.864 --> 30:52.630
Harvey, we need to talk.

30:52.632 --> 30:54.165
Mike just told me you're
breaking a deal with him.

30:54.167 --> 30:55.667
Well, he shouldn't have
told you that,

30:55.669 --> 30:56.835
because that's none
of your business.

30:56.837 --> 30:58.536
None of my business?

30:58.538 --> 31:00.104
My name's on the wall
as much as yours.

31:00.106 --> 31:02.507
Look, if Mike
doesn't drop that case,

31:02.509 --> 31:03.775
we lose a major client.

31:03.777 --> 31:05.643
I can't have that.
- No, Harvey.

31:05.645 --> 31:07.545
What we can't have is
you setting a precedent

31:07.547 --> 31:10.615
that Alex's clients can run
roughshod all over us.

31:10.617 --> 31:11.616
Keep your voices down.

31:11.618 --> 31:13.518
Oh, I get it.

31:13.520 --> 31:15.086
So this isn't about me
breaking my deal with Mike.

31:15.088 --> 31:17.088
This is about you being
jealous of Alex.

31:17.090 --> 31:18.823
No, it isn't.
I thought it was a mistake

31:18.825 --> 31:20.692
even before I found out
that it was Alex's client.

31:20.694 --> 31:22.527
- Harvey, he has a point.
- Bullshit.

31:22.529 --> 31:24.262
You told me you were afraid
that I was gonna become

31:24.264 --> 31:26.865
better friends with him than
you, and that's what this is.

31:26.867 --> 31:29.667
How dare you say that to me in
front of Donna?

31:29.669 --> 31:33.705
I told you that in
complete confidence.

31:33.707 --> 31:36.207
This isn't about my
relationship with Alex.

31:36.209 --> 31:37.842
This is about your
relationship with Alex

31:37.844 --> 31:39.677
and how you're afraid
to stand up to him.

31:39.679 --> 31:41.679
You want to run that
by me again?

31:41.681 --> 31:43.214
I just ran it by you.

31:43.216 --> 31:45.216
What you are doing
is a mistake.

31:45.218 --> 31:46.718
I don't think so,

31:46.720 --> 31:48.586
and Donna doesn't think so,
which means--

31:48.588 --> 31:50.522
Actually, Harvey, I do.

31:50.524 --> 31:52.624
And if it's all the same to you,
I can speak for myself.

31:52.626 --> 31:55.660
- Are you kidding me?
- No, I'm not.

31:55.662 --> 31:57.795
Because the last time you said
if I had something to say,

31:57.797 --> 31:59.230
say it in the goddamn meeting.

31:59.232 --> 32:01.199
Well, this is the goddamn
meeting.

32:01.201 --> 32:03.134
And I happen to think we should
keep our word to Mike

32:03.136 --> 32:04.736
instead of letting some client
bully us.

32:04.738 --> 32:06.738
Well, I appreciate the input.

32:06.740 --> 32:08.940
But I told you you'd
get a vote

32:08.942 --> 32:11.109
when I said there'd be a vote,

32:11.111 --> 32:12.710
and this isn't a vote.

32:12.712 --> 32:15.313
As for you, take a look
in the mirror,

32:15.315 --> 32:18.316
because the only reason
that you're pissed about this

32:18.318 --> 32:21.586
is your new honeysuckle friend
canceled lunch on you for me.

32:21.588 --> 32:24.589
<i>[solemn music]</i>

32:24.591 --> 32:29.594
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:29.596 --> 32:31.195
Louis...

32:39.672 --> 32:41.241
Aren't you a little old to be
spending your break

32:41.243 --> 32:43.143
in a comic book store?

32:43.145 --> 32:44.278
Everybody has their
hobbies, Mike.

32:44.280 --> 32:45.479
Mine's comics.

32:45.481 --> 32:47.147
Yours is helping big
corporations

32:47.149 --> 32:48.482
screw over the little guy.

32:50.186 --> 32:52.586
Oliver, wait.

32:52.588 --> 32:55.422
I just, I came here
because I owe you an apology,

32:55.424 --> 32:58.158
and...
this is my way of doing it.

32:58.160 --> 32:59.426
What's that?

32:59.428 --> 33:01.161
More money
to make everything okay?

33:01.163 --> 33:03.530
It's a case.
It's one that means a lot to me.

33:03.532 --> 33:05.566
It's about a guy
who died in prison.

33:05.568 --> 33:07.568
If it means so much to you,
why don't you do it yourself?

33:07.570 --> 33:09.570
I can't.

33:09.572 --> 33:12.573
We have a conflict
with one of our clients.

33:12.575 --> 33:15.442
Well, that's a nice speech,
Mike, but I'm not interested,

33:15.444 --> 33:17.511
because there's something in it
for you, like always.

33:17.513 --> 33:18.879
Oliver, please,
look, before you say no,

33:18.881 --> 33:20.447
just listen
to what I have to say.

33:20.449 --> 33:22.449
I don't need to listen
to you anymore.

33:22.451 --> 33:24.318
God damn it,
I almost died in there.

33:28.357 --> 33:30.424
What?

33:34.196 --> 33:35.496
My second night in Danbury,

33:35.498 --> 33:37.498
I thought
that someone was gonna kill me.

33:37.500 --> 33:39.199
And then my last night,

33:39.201 --> 33:42.136
I knew that same guy
was coming for me again.

33:42.138 --> 33:43.637
But I got out.

33:45.207 --> 33:47.174
This kid didn't.

33:48.210 --> 33:49.710
The only thing
that's in this for me

33:49.712 --> 33:53.547
is making sure that this
doesn't happen to someone else.

33:53.549 --> 34:00.220
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:00.222 --> 34:01.622
This seems
pretty cut-and-dry, Mike.

34:01.624 --> 34:04.358
That's how they want it
to look.

34:04.360 --> 34:05.492
I already know they didn't have
enough guard staff

34:05.494 --> 34:07.461
on duty that night.

34:08.597 --> 34:09.730
Which means
they probably didn't have

34:09.732 --> 34:11.231
enough medical staff either.

34:11.233 --> 34:12.733
Or maybe none at all.

34:12.735 --> 34:14.935
Look, I can't let them
get away with this

34:14.937 --> 34:16.503
without handing it off
to the one lawyer

34:16.505 --> 34:18.672
I know cares enough
to see it through.

34:18.674 --> 34:21.742
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:21.744 --> 34:24.378
Okay, Mike.

34:24.380 --> 34:25.679
I'm in.

34:25.681 --> 34:27.581
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:31.253 --> 34:34.288
- Donna, whatever it is--
- Rachel, I'm so sorry.

34:34.290 --> 34:35.722
What I did was wrong
and horrible

34:35.724 --> 34:37.424
and showed you no respect,

34:37.426 --> 34:38.759
and then you came
and tried to tell me that,

34:38.761 --> 34:41.395
and I made it
a thousand times worse.

34:41.397 --> 34:44.264
Why would you do something
like that in the first place?

34:44.266 --> 34:45.632
'Cause I'm new at this.

34:46.768 --> 34:48.668
Then I saw Stephanie
treating you like shit,

34:48.670 --> 34:51.538
and it felt like
she was doing that to me.

34:51.540 --> 34:53.674
Because you're the one
that gave me the job.

34:53.676 --> 34:56.275
Maybe.

34:56.277 --> 34:57.678
And then you told me
I cut your legs out,

34:57.680 --> 34:59.446
and that made me
feel even worse,

34:59.448 --> 35:00.681
and I took it out on you.

35:00.683 --> 35:02.616
- Donna--
- Rachel, you were right.

35:02.618 --> 35:04.718
I'm not completely ready
for this.

35:06.789 --> 35:08.555
And I'm not always
gonna get things right,

35:08.557 --> 35:11.658
and I got them
really wrong today.

35:14.296 --> 35:16.463
Maybe not all wrong.

35:16.465 --> 35:18.565
What do you mean?

35:20.569 --> 35:23.337
I thought about it too.

35:23.339 --> 35:28.675
I am finally a member
of the bar.

35:33.749 --> 35:36.316
I don't want to supervise
anyone right now.

35:36.318 --> 35:39.019
I just want to be
the best lawyer I can be.

35:39.021 --> 35:40.854
I understand.

35:42.458 --> 35:44.825
I'll take care of
the associates for now.

35:46.462 --> 35:47.828
Donna.

35:47.830 --> 35:49.496
What made you realize all that?

35:49.498 --> 35:50.797
Let's just say

35:50.799 --> 35:52.733
I was reminded
what it feels like

35:52.735 --> 35:54.835
when someone speaks for you
and what they're saying

35:54.837 --> 35:58.338
is the complete opposite
of what you wanted to say.

35:58.340 --> 36:00.841
- Louis?
- Harvey.

36:00.843 --> 36:03.644
The one who gave you
your new position.

36:03.646 --> 36:05.312
Exactly.

36:05.314 --> 36:07.514
I'm so sorry, Donna.

36:07.516 --> 36:09.516
I'm sorry too, Rachel.

36:09.518 --> 36:14.588
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:17.459 --> 36:18.859
Harvey, it's late.
Whatever it is--

36:18.861 --> 36:22.629
Did you pawn that thing off
to the clinic?

36:22.631 --> 36:24.464
You asked me to drop it,
so I dropped it.

36:24.466 --> 36:26.366
Bullshit.

36:26.368 --> 36:27.734
You gave it to the clinic
you're affiliated with.

36:27.736 --> 36:29.469
The clinic you told me
I could give cases to

36:29.471 --> 36:30.604
at my discretion.

36:30.606 --> 36:32.539
Maybe you missed the memo.

36:32.541 --> 36:35.375
If our firm is in any way
associated with that case,

36:35.377 --> 36:36.576
we lose a huge client.

36:36.578 --> 36:38.078
Harvey, I'm not working on it.

36:38.080 --> 36:39.780
Then you're gonna put that
in writing,

36:39.782 --> 36:40.881
and you're gonna deliver it
to Alex's client.

36:40.883 --> 36:42.616
Ironclad Chinese wall.

36:42.618 --> 36:43.917
You have nothing to do
with this case.

36:43.919 --> 36:46.453
Are you saying
you don't trust me?

36:46.455 --> 36:47.654
You saying you didn't know
what you were doing

36:47.656 --> 36:49.623
when you gave it to the clinic?

36:51.894 --> 36:53.660
Okay, Harvey.

36:53.662 --> 36:55.362
I'll put it in writing.

36:57.399 --> 36:58.532
I want you word
you're gonna live

36:58.534 --> 37:00.367
by what you sign.

37:00.369 --> 37:01.802
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:01.804 --> 37:03.537
You have my word.

37:03.539 --> 37:08.375
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:09.912 --> 37:11.912
You wanted to see me?

37:11.914 --> 37:13.814
Yes, I did,
I was just wondering,

37:13.816 --> 37:17.684
have you redone the assignment
that Rachel gave you?

37:17.686 --> 37:18.719
Not yet.

37:18.721 --> 37:20.787
I had a ton on my plate.

37:20.789 --> 37:22.889
I was gonna get to it tomorrow.

37:24.827 --> 37:26.460
You're fired.

37:27.563 --> 37:29.963
Please,
I-I really was going to do it.

37:29.965 --> 37:31.832
I believe you.

37:31.834 --> 37:33.700
But my rule is
three strikes and you're out.

37:33.702 --> 37:35.936
Otherwise, where does it end?

37:35.938 --> 37:38.572
In that case,
why not do this publicly?

37:38.574 --> 37:40.841
I don't need to do this
publicly, Stephanie.

37:40.843 --> 37:43.844
When you're not here tomorrow,
people will know what happened.

37:43.846 --> 37:47.714
But I do want you to know,
I wish you well.

37:47.716 --> 37:49.950
Do you expect me
to believe that?

37:49.952 --> 37:51.451
I don't know.

37:51.453 --> 37:52.953
But it's true.

37:52.955 --> 38:00.427
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:02.000 --> 38:08.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

38:09.605 --> 38:11.438
Before you say anything,

38:11.440 --> 38:12.973
I came here for a reason.

38:12.975 --> 38:14.975
Because this is where we met,

38:14.977 --> 38:17.444
but it isn't where
I need to be anymore.

38:17.446 --> 38:18.812
Harvey, I don't think--

38:18.814 --> 38:20.647
I just have one question
to ask you.

38:20.649 --> 38:22.983
Are you worried about
what this woman's gonna think

38:22.985 --> 38:24.985
or because you think
what we're doing is wrong?

38:24.987 --> 38:27.621
Because if this is just about
what other people think,

38:27.623 --> 38:28.789
it's crazy.

38:28.791 --> 38:30.891
Well, it isn't crazy to me,

38:30.893 --> 38:31.958
and I need you
to understand that.

38:31.960 --> 38:33.593
I do understand that,

38:33.595 --> 38:34.995
but I also know
we have a connection,

38:34.997 --> 38:36.763
and to throw that away

38:36.765 --> 38:38.799
because of some figment
of your imagination--

38:38.801 --> 38:41.501
It is not a figment
of my imagination.

38:41.503 --> 38:43.503
And I'm not worried
about what she thinks.

38:43.505 --> 38:46.673
I am worried about what I think.
- And what is it that you think?

38:46.675 --> 38:48.742
That what if this was
a terrible mistake

38:48.744 --> 38:50.544
and it doesn't work out

38:50.546 --> 38:52.612
and I look like a fool?

38:54.016 --> 38:56.016
Okay.

38:56.018 --> 38:59.553
I know
I'm not the therapist here,

38:59.555 --> 39:01.822
but isn't that the risk
of any relationship?

39:01.824 --> 39:04.691
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:04.693 --> 39:07.594
I'm scared, Harvey.

39:07.596 --> 39:08.862
Me too.

39:08.864 --> 39:10.931
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:10.933 --> 39:13.600
What do you say
we both be scared together?

39:13.602 --> 39:16.603
<i>[vocal pop music]</i>

39:16.605 --> 39:21.675
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:21.677 --> 39:24.544
Can I help you?

39:24.546 --> 39:25.946
Yeah.

39:25.948 --> 39:28.014
My name is Mike Ross.

39:28.016 --> 39:29.850
I would say nice to meet you,

39:29.852 --> 39:31.952
but I'm pretty sure
you don't feel the same way.

39:31.954 --> 39:34.254
Not particularly.

39:34.256 --> 39:35.755
What's this?

39:35.757 --> 39:37.991
My next 15 potential lawsuits.

39:37.993 --> 39:39.059
I just want to make sure
you don't have any conflicts

39:39.061 --> 39:40.560
with any of these.

39:40.562 --> 39:41.828
Maybe your client's grandmother

39:41.830 --> 39:43.563
shops at the supermarket

39:43.565 --> 39:45.065
across the street
from number 12.

39:45.067 --> 39:47.701
I'll take a look.

39:47.703 --> 39:49.569
Good, 'cause just to be clear,

39:49.571 --> 39:50.804
if I'd known
there was a conflict,

39:50.806 --> 39:52.806
I never would've taken the case.

39:54.076 --> 39:55.942
I appreciate you dropping it.

39:55.944 --> 39:57.844
I was bulldozed
into dropping it,

39:57.846 --> 40:00.680
just like I was bulldozed
into signing this.

40:01.984 --> 40:04.584
Now, I can live with
both those things,

40:04.586 --> 40:06.019
but I never want to get caught
in this situation again.

40:06.021 --> 40:09.623
- [chuckles]
- What's so funny?

40:09.625 --> 40:12.626
I just told my client
the same damn thing.

40:12.628 --> 40:14.628
Bullshit.

40:14.630 --> 40:16.129
You think
this makes me look good?

40:17.866 --> 40:20.700
Well then I guess we're in
the same boat after all.

40:20.702 --> 40:21.801
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:21.803 --> 40:23.703
It's nice to meet you, Mike.

40:24.873 --> 40:26.540
Welcome
to Pearson Specter Litt.

40:26.542 --> 40:28.875
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:28.877 --> 40:31.912
<i>You said I needed a strategy</i>
<i>for when it happened.</i>

40:31.914 --> 40:34.014
Well, I used your strategy,
and I got over it,

40:34.016 --> 40:36.116
but it didn't fix
a goddamn thing!

40:36.118 --> 40:40.153
Louis, calm down.
I'm here for you.

40:40.155 --> 40:42.122
No, you're not!
You're never there for me.

40:42.124 --> 40:43.790
You're always against me.

40:43.792 --> 40:45.759
<i>I did what you said,</i>

40:45.761 --> 40:47.794
<i>and this time,</i>
<i>it's not my fault.</i>

40:47.796 --> 40:50.897
And I don't give a shit
what you think.

40:50.899 --> 40:53.133
I'm not the horrible person
you always say I am.

40:53.135 --> 40:55.135
Louis, I don't think
you're a horrible person.

40:55.137 --> 40:57.137
I think
you're a wonderful person.

40:57.139 --> 40:58.939
And if I haven't made
that clear to you,

40:58.941 --> 41:00.707
I am very sorry.

41:00.709 --> 41:02.809
Well, you can be sorry
all you want, Harvey.

41:02.811 --> 41:04.811
- Louis?
<i>- But you are wrong about me.</i>

41:04.813 --> 41:07.681
I'm not
a worthless piece of shit.

41:07.683 --> 41:09.182
<i>You failed me.</i>

41:10.085 --> 41:12.085
And you were wrong.

41:12.087 --> 41:13.987
<i>You were wrong!</i>
<i>[phone slams]</i>

